#. <section class="sutta" id="sn12.67"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn12.67:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 12"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 12"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.67:0.2"
msgid "7. Mahāvagga"
msgstr "7. The Great Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 67. Naḷakalāpīsutta → naḷakalāpasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn12.67:0.3"
msgid "67. Naḷakalāpīsutta"
msgstr "67. Bundles of Reeds"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.113"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: mahākoṭṭhiko → mahākoṭṭhito (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn12.67:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ca sāriputto āyasmā ca mahākoṭṭhiko bārāṇasiyaṃ "
"viharanti isipatane migadāye."
msgstr ""
"At one time Venerable Sāriputta and Venerable Mahākoṭṭhita were staying near "
"Benares, in the deer park at Isipatana."

msgctxt "sn12.67:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā mahākoṭṭhiko sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yenāyasmā "
"sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā sāriputtena saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Then in the late afternoon, Venerable Mahākoṭṭhita came out of retreat, went "
"to Venerable Sāriputta, and exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "sn12.67:1.3"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho āyasmā mahākoṭṭhiko āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side and said to Sāriputta:"

msgctxt "sn12.67:1.4"
msgid ""
"“kiṃ nu kho, āvuso sāriputta, sayaṃkataṃ jarāmaraṇaṃ, paraṃkataṃ "
"jarāmaraṇaṃ, sayaṃkatañca paraṃkatañca jarāmaraṇaṃ, udāhu asayaṃkāraṃ "
"aparaṅkāraṃ adhiccasamuppannaṃ jarāmaraṇan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Well, Reverend Sāriputta, are old age and death made by oneself? Or by "
"another? Or by both oneself and another? Or do they arise by chance, not "
"made by oneself or another?”"

msgctxt "sn12.67:1.5"
msgid ""
"“Na kho, āvuso koṭṭhika, sayaṃkataṃ jarāmaraṇaṃ, na paraṃkataṃ jarāmaraṇaṃ, "
"na sayaṃkatañca paraṃkatañca jarāmaraṇaṃ, nāpi asayaṃkāraṃ aparaṅkāraṃ "
"adhiccasamuppannaṃ jarāmaraṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“No, Reverend Koṭṭhita, old age and death are not made by oneself, nor by "
"another, nor by both oneself and another, nor do they arise by chance, not "
"made by oneself or another."

msgctxt "sn12.67:1.6"
msgid "Api ca jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇan”ti."
msgstr "Rather, rebirth is a condition for old age and death.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.67:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso sāriputta, sayaṅkatā jāti, paraṅkatā jāti, sayaṅkatā ca "
"paraṅkatā ca jāti, udāhu asayaṅkārā aparaṅkārā adhiccasamuppannā jātī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Well, Reverend Sāriputta, is rebirth made by oneself? Or by another? Or by "
"both oneself and another? Or does it arise by chance, not made by oneself or "
"another?”"

msgctxt "sn12.67:2.2"
msgid ""
"“Na kho, āvuso koṭṭhika, sayaṅkatā jāti, na paraṅkatā jāti, na sayaṅkatā ca "
"paraṅkatā ca jāti, nāpi asayaṅkārā aparaṅkārā adhiccasamuppannā jāti."
msgstr ""
"“No, Reverend Koṭṭhita, rebirth is not made by oneself, nor by another, nor "
"by both oneself and another, nor does it arise by chance, not made by "
"oneself or another."

msgctxt "sn12.67:2.3"
msgid "Api ca bhavapaccayā jātī”ti."
msgstr "Rather, continued existence is a condition for rebirth.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.67:3.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso sāriputta, sayaṅkato bhavo … pe …"
msgstr "“Well, Reverend Sāriputta, is continued existence made by oneself? …” …"

msgctxt "sn12.67:3.2"
msgid "sayaṅkataṃ upādānaṃ …"
msgstr "“Is grasping made by oneself? …” …"

msgctxt "sn12.67:3.3"
msgid "sayaṅkatā taṇhā …"
msgstr "“Is craving made by oneself? …” …"

msgctxt "sn12.67:3.4"
msgid "sayaṅkatā vedanā …"
msgstr "“Is feeling made by oneself? …” …"

msgctxt "sn12.67:3.5"
msgid "sayaṅkato phasso …"
msgstr "“Is contact made by oneself? …” …"

msgctxt "sn12.67:3.6"
msgid "sayaṅkataṃ saḷāyatanaṃ …"
msgstr "“Are the six sense fields made by oneself? …” …"

msgctxt "sn12.67:3.7"
msgid ""
"sayaṅkataṃ nāmarūpaṃ, paraṅkataṃ nāmarūpaṃ, sayaṅkatañca paraṅkatañca "
"nāmarūpaṃ, udāhu asayaṅkāraṃ aparaṅkāraṃ adhiccasamuppannaṃ nāmarūpan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Well, Reverend Sāriputta, are name and form made by oneself? Or by another? "
"Or by both oneself and another? Or do they arise by chance, not made by "
"oneself or another?”"

msgctxt "sn12.67:3.8"
msgid ""
"“Na kho, āvuso koṭṭhika, sayaṅkataṃ nāmarūpaṃ, na paraṅkataṃ nāmarūpaṃ, na "
"sayaṅkatañca paraṅkatañca nāmarūpaṃ, nāpi asayaṅkāraṃ aparaṅkāraṃ, "
"adhiccasamuppannaṃ nāmarūpaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“No, Reverend Koṭṭhita, name and form are not made by oneself, nor by "
"another, nor by both oneself and another, nor do they arise by chance, not "
"made by oneself or another."

msgctxt "sn12.67:3.9"
msgid "Api ca viññāṇapaccayā nāmarūpan”ti."
msgstr "Rather, consciousness is a condition for name and form.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.67:4.1"
msgid ""
"“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso sāriputta, sayaṅkataṃ viññāṇaṃ, paraṅkataṃ viññāṇaṃ, "
"sayaṅkatañca paraṅkatañca viññāṇaṃ, udāhu asayaṅkāraṃ aparaṅkāraṃ "
"adhiccasamuppannaṃ viññāṇan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Well, Reverend Sāriputta, is consciousness made by oneself? Or by another? "
"Or by both oneself and another? Or does it arise by chance, not made by "
"oneself or another?”"

msgctxt "sn12.67:4.2"
msgid ""
"“Na kho, āvuso koṭṭhika, sayaṅkataṃ viññāṇaṃ, na paraṅkataṃ viññāṇaṃ, na "
"sayaṅkatañca paraṅkatañca viññāṇaṃ, nāpi asayaṅkāraṃ aparaṅkāraṃ "
"adhiccasamuppannaṃ viññāṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“No, Reverend Koṭṭhita, consciousness is not made by oneself, nor by "
"another, nor by both oneself and another, nor does it arise by chance, not "
"made by oneself or another."

msgctxt "sn12.67:4.3"
msgid "Api ca nāmarūpapaccayā viññāṇan”ti."
msgstr "Rather, name and form are conditions for consciousness.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.114"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.67:5.1"
msgid "“Idāneva kho mayaṃ āyasmato sāriputtassa bhāsitaṃ evaṃ ājānāma:"
msgstr "“Just now I understood you to say:"

msgctxt "sn12.67:5.2"
msgid ""
"‘na khvāvuso koṭṭhika, sayaṅkataṃ nāmarūpaṃ, na paraṅkataṃ nāmarūpaṃ, na "
"sayaṅkatañca paraṅkatañca nāmarūpaṃ, nāpi asayaṅkāraṃ aparaṅkāraṃ "
"adhiccasamuppannaṃ nāmarūpaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘No, Reverend Koṭṭhita, name and form are not made by oneself, nor by "
"another, nor by both oneself and another, nor do they arise by chance, not "
"made by oneself or another."

msgctxt "sn12.67:5.3"
msgid "Api ca viññāṇapaccayā nāmarūpan’ti."
msgstr "Rather, consciousness is a condition for name and form.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.67:6.1"
msgid "Idāneva ca pana mayaṃ āyasmato sāriputtassa bhāsitaṃ evaṃ ājānāma:"
msgstr "But I also understood you to say:"

msgctxt "sn12.67:6.2"
msgid ""
"‘na khvāvuso koṭṭhika, sayaṅkataṃ viññāṇaṃ, na paraṅkataṃ viññāṇaṃ, na "
"sayaṅkatañca paraṅkatañca viññāṇaṃ, nāpi asayaṅkāraṃ aparaṅkāraṃ "
"adhiccasamuppannaṃ viññāṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘No, Reverend Koṭṭhita, consciousness is not made by oneself, nor by "
"another, nor by both oneself and another, nor does it arise by chance, not "
"made by oneself or another."

msgctxt "sn12.67:6.3"
msgid "Api ca nāmarūpapaccayā viññāṇan’ti."
msgstr "Rather, name and form are conditions for consciousness.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.67:7.1"
msgid "Yathā kathaṃ panāvuso sāriputta, imassa bhāsitassa attho daṭṭhabbo”ti?"
msgstr "How then should we see the meaning of this statement?”"

msgctxt "sn12.67:7.2"
msgid "“Tenahāvuso, upamaṃ te karissāmi."
msgstr "“Well then, reverend, I shall give you a simile."

msgctxt "sn12.67:7.3"
msgid "Upamāyapidhekacce viññū purisā bhāsitassa atthaṃ jānanti."
msgstr ""
"For by means of a simile some sensible people understand the meaning of what "
"is said."

msgctxt "sn12.67:7.4"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, āvuso, dve naḷakalāpiyo aññamaññaṃ nissāya tiṭṭheyyuṃ."
msgstr "Suppose there were two bundles of reeds leaning up against each other."

msgctxt "sn12.67:7.5"
msgid "Evameva kho, āvuso, nāmarūpapaccayā viññāṇaṃ;"
msgstr "In the same way, name and form are conditions for consciousness."

msgctxt "sn12.67:7.6"
msgid "viññāṇapaccayā nāmarūpaṃ;"
msgstr "Consciousness is a condition for name and form."

msgctxt "sn12.67:7.7"
msgid "nāmarūpapaccayā saḷāyatanaṃ;"
msgstr "Name and form are conditions for the six sense fields."

msgctxt "sn12.67:7.8"
msgid "saḷāyatanapaccayā phasso … pe …"
msgstr "The six sense fields are conditions for contact. …"

msgctxt "sn12.67:7.9"
msgid "evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti."
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates."

msgctxt "sn12.67:7.10"
msgid "Tāsañce, āvuso, naḷakalāpīnaṃ ekaṃ ākaḍḍheyya, ekā papateyya;"
msgstr ""
"If the first of those bundles of reeds were to be pulled away, the other "
"would collapse."

msgctxt "sn12.67:7.11"
msgid "aparañce ākaḍḍheyya, aparā papateyya."
msgstr "And if the other were to be pulled away, the first would collapse."

msgctxt "sn12.67:7.12"
msgid "Evameva kho, āvuso, nāmarūpanirodhā viññāṇanirodho;"
msgstr "In the same way, when name and form cease, consciousness ceases."

msgctxt "sn12.67:7.13"
msgid "viññāṇanirodhā nāmarūpanirodho;"
msgstr "When consciousness ceases, name and form cease."

msgctxt "sn12.67:7.14"
msgid "nāmarūpanirodhā saḷāyatananirodho;"
msgstr "When name and form cease, the six sense fields cease."

msgctxt "sn12.67:7.15"
msgid "saḷāyatananirodhā phassanirodho … pe …"
msgstr "When the six sense fields cease, contact ceases. …"

msgctxt "sn12.67:7.16"
msgid "evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hotī”ti."
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.67:8.1"
msgid "“Acchariyaṃ, āvuso sāriputta;"
msgstr "“It’s incredible, Reverend Sāriputta, it’s amazing!"

msgctxt "sn12.67:8.2"
msgid "abbhutaṃ, āvuso sāriputta."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.67:8.3"
msgid "Yāvasubhāsitañcidaṃ āyasmatā sāriputtena."
msgstr "How well spoken this was by Venerable Sāriputta!"

msgctxt "sn12.67:8.4"
msgid ""
"Idañca pana mayaṃ āyasmato sāriputtassa bhāsitaṃ imehi chattiṃsāya vatthūhi "
"anumodāma:"
msgstr ""
"And we can express our agreement with Venerable Sāriputta’s statement on "
"these thirty-six grounds."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.115"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.67:9.1"
msgid ""
"‘Jarāmaraṇassa ce, āvuso, bhikkhu nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya dhammaṃ "
"deseti, dhammakathiko bhikkhūti alaṃvacanāya."
msgstr ""
"If a mendicant teaches Dhamma for disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation "
"regarding old age and death, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant who "
"speaks on Dhamma’."

msgctxt "sn12.67:9.2"
msgid ""
"Jarāmaraṇassa ce, āvuso, bhikkhu nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya paṭipanno "
"hoti, dhammānudhammappaṭipanno bhikkhūti alaṃvacanāya."
msgstr ""
"If they practice for disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding "
"old age and death, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant who practices "
"in line with the teaching’."

msgctxt "sn12.67:9.3"
msgid ""
"Jarāmaraṇassa ce, āvuso, bhikkhu nibbidā virāgā nirodhā anupādā vimutto "
"hoti, diṭṭhadhammanibbānappatto bhikkhūti alaṃvacanāya."
msgstr ""
"If they’re freed by not grasping by disillusionment, dispassion, and "
"cessation regarding old age and death, they’re qualified to be called a ‘"
"mendicant who has attained extinguishment in this very life’."

msgctxt "sn12.67:9.4"
msgid "Jātiyā ce …"
msgstr "If a mendicant teaches Dhamma for disillusionment regarding rebirth …"

msgctxt "sn12.67:9.5"
msgid "bhavassa ce …"
msgstr "continued existence …"

msgctxt "sn12.67:9.6"
msgid "upādānassa ce …"
msgstr "grasping …"

msgctxt "sn12.67:9.7"
msgid "taṇhāya ce …"
msgstr "craving …"

msgctxt "sn12.67:9.8"
msgid "vedanāya ce …"
msgstr "feeling …"

msgctxt "sn12.67:9.9"
msgid "phassassa ce …"
msgstr "contact …"

msgctxt "sn12.67:9.10"
msgid "saḷāyatanassa ce …"
msgstr "the six sense fields …"

msgctxt "sn12.67:9.11"
msgid "nāmarūpassa ce …"
msgstr "name and form …"

msgctxt "sn12.67:9.12"
msgid "viññāṇassa ce …"
msgstr "consciousness …"

msgctxt "sn12.67:9.13"
msgid "saṅkhārānañce …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn12.67:9.14"
msgid ""
"avijjāya ce, āvuso, bhikkhu nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya dhammaṃ deseti, "
"dhammakathiko bhikkhūti alaṃvacanāya."
msgstr ""
"If a mendicant teaches Dhamma for disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation "
"regarding ignorance, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant who speaks "
"on Dhamma’."

msgctxt "sn12.67:9.15"
msgid ""
"Avijjāya ce, āvuso, bhikkhu nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti, "
"dhammānudhammappaṭipanno bhikkhūti alaṃvacanāya."
msgstr ""
"If they practice for disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding "
"ignorance, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant who practices in line "
"with the teaching’."

msgctxt "sn12.67:9.16"
msgid ""
"Avijjāya ce, āvuso, bhikkhu nibbidā virāgā nirodhā anupādā vimutto hoti, "
"diṭṭhadhammanibbānappatto bhikkhūti alaṃvacanāyā’”ti."
msgstr ""
"If they’re freed by not grasping by disillusionment, dispassion, and "
"cessation regarding ignorance, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant "
"who has attained extinguishment in this very life’.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn12.67:9.17"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
